WEBVTT

00:09.053 --> 00:11.011
♪♪

01:15.470 --> 01:16.929
[doors close]

01:19.011 --> 01:21.512
[officer] These are the guns
seized at Bromley Heath.

01:21.512 --> 01:22.845
Twelve-gauge pump.

01:22.845 --> 01:24.303
MP 40.

01:24.303 --> 01:26.303
One Colt 1911.

01:26.303 --> 01:28.345
Two Ruger 38's.

01:28.345 --> 01:30.220
One Glock 9 mil.

01:30.220 --> 01:32.428
And that's the AK.

01:32.428 --> 01:34.178
I gotta take this
to the lab.

01:35.595 --> 01:37.220
[door opens]

01:37.220 --> 01:39.136
[Hank]
The Bromley Heath arrests,

01:39.136 --> 01:41.345
they have priors.

01:41.345 --> 01:43.512
Two of them did gladiator
training at Canterbury

01:43.512 --> 01:45.053
as juveniles.

01:45.053 --> 01:46.387
The other one was tried
as an adult,

01:46.387 --> 01:48.136
but the conviction
was overturned.

01:48.136 --> 01:50.512
Proving Lady Justice
isn't truly blind.

01:50.512 --> 01:53.053
[Jackie] Decourcy Ward,
you fucking hypocrite.

01:53.053 --> 01:54.470
[Decourcy]
This coming from the guy

01:54.470 --> 01:56.387
who woulda underbid Judas
to betray Jesus?

01:56.387 --> 01:58.970
You're dumping on your own.
You're presupposing their guilt

01:58.970 --> 02:01.929
-because they're black.
-The fuck you say to me?

02:01.929 --> 02:03.970
Ain't 'cause they're black.

02:03.970 --> 02:06.178
It's about the facts.
Look at the rap sheet.

02:06.178 --> 02:08.136
I don't like to think about it
like that,

02:08.136 --> 02:10.303
but at least I'm honest enough
to say what's probably true.

02:10.303 --> 02:12.345
Indians used to kill
retarded babies.

02:12.345 --> 02:13.679
[Hank]
And we're off.

02:13.679 --> 02:15.970
[Jackie] Nope.
I read this in a book.

02:15.970 --> 02:17.845
The little red kid
came out bent,

02:17.845 --> 02:20.720
twisted with a fucked-up foot
or a funny lip,

02:20.720 --> 02:22.053
they had no use for him.

02:22.053 --> 02:24.553
They didn't think twice.
Into the river.

02:24.553 --> 02:26.470
Oh, shit,
what'd I walk into?

02:26.470 --> 02:28.679
Nothing. Just a man
looking in the mirror,

02:28.679 --> 02:30.303
not liking what he sees.

02:30.303 --> 02:32.220
That mirror looks both ways,
Jackie.

02:32.220 --> 02:34.345
And I'm on the other side of it
looking at you,

02:34.345 --> 02:36.428
judging your fucked-up brothers
in Charlestown

02:36.428 --> 02:38.845
same way as I judge
these boys in Roxbury.

02:38.845 --> 02:40.887
Oh, no, no, no, no, no.
That's different.

02:40.887 --> 02:42.887
-How so?
-'Cause...

02:42.887 --> 02:45.637
you believe
in rehabilitation.

02:45.637 --> 02:47.261
Second chances.

02:47.261 --> 02:49.929
Time off for good behavior.
I say black or white,

02:49.929 --> 02:52.720
throw the whole lousy bunch
of them into the fucking river.

02:52.720 --> 02:54.637
Anyone want to hear
the lab report?

02:54.637 --> 02:56.011
Please.

02:56.011 --> 02:59.178
Ballistics can't yet match
the 7.62 mm round

02:59.178 --> 03:01.345
taken from the armored truck

03:01.345 --> 03:04.220
to the AK seized
at Bromley Heath.

03:04.220 --> 03:05.845
-Shit.
-You sure?

03:05.845 --> 03:07.387
Bullshit. Who fucking cares?

03:07.387 --> 03:09.553
[Hank] We need something
before Decourcy can reconvene

03:09.553 --> 03:11.220
-the grand jury.
-No, no, no, no.

03:11.220 --> 03:13.053
I'm calling bullshit.

03:13.053 --> 03:14.637
The grand jury doesn't know

03:14.637 --> 03:15.887
that we don't have a match
on the fuckin' bullet,

03:15.887 --> 03:17.303
and they're a grand jury.

03:17.303 --> 03:18.720
They're prone to
believing the worst.

03:18.720 --> 03:20.345
I swear on my dick

03:20.345 --> 03:22.220
we're going to get
a match on that fragment.

03:22.220 --> 03:24.679
But in the meantime,
we keep fucking pressing.

03:24.679 --> 03:27.887
This is why FBI stands
for "Fucking Bunch of Idiots."

03:27.887 --> 03:30.261
County Sheriff's Department
doesn't just date-rape their way

03:30.261 --> 03:33.178
into a case
hoping for the best.

03:33.178 --> 03:35.345
And your conviction rates
prove that.

03:35.345 --> 03:38.011
[Decourcy]
Hey.

03:38.011 --> 03:39.679
I know this kid.
Ziba Pippin.

03:41.261 --> 03:44.845
[Decourcy]
United States Code 18.922.

03:44.845 --> 03:48.428
Mandatory sentencing
for gun trafficking's 15 years.

03:50.053 --> 03:51.970
Fifteen.

03:51.970 --> 03:55.261
You add murder, you serve
your whole time on earth.

03:56.762 --> 03:58.970
Oh, you tired,
Mr. Pippin?

03:58.970 --> 04:01.637
Of this bullshit, yeah.

04:01.637 --> 04:03.512
[scoffs]

04:03.512 --> 04:07.178
There you are, serving me this
fucked-up code of silence.

04:07.178 --> 04:09.929
The AK-47 found
in your apartment

04:09.929 --> 04:12.053
was used to execute
three white guards

04:12.053 --> 04:13.887
in an armored car robbery.

04:13.887 --> 04:15.428
Look at my sheet.

04:15.428 --> 04:19.011
See "armored car robbery"
among my many achievements?

04:20.970 --> 04:23.303
Did you ever think about
where those guns came from?

04:24.845 --> 04:27.428
That maybe those
Charlestown cowboys

04:27.428 --> 04:29.303
wanted you to have it
so they could blame you

04:29.303 --> 04:32.053
for the deaths of those three
white guards, hmm?

04:32.053 --> 04:34.762
Prison ain't shit to me.

04:40.720 --> 04:42.136
♪♪

04:42.136 --> 04:44.303
[Decourcy sighs]

04:46.762 --> 04:49.470
You don't recognize me,
do you?

04:49.470 --> 04:52.261
All assholes
look alike.

04:53.261 --> 04:55.720
I know you from church.

04:56.887 --> 04:58.553
I know your mom.

04:58.553 --> 05:00.136
Delia Pippin.

05:00.136 --> 05:02.303
Works at Ronnie's Market.

05:03.679 --> 05:05.428
Nice woman.

05:05.428 --> 05:07.470
Doesn't earn much money,
though.

05:08.804 --> 05:10.178
To make ends meet,

05:10.178 --> 05:12.345
she wholesales food
out the back door.

05:12.345 --> 05:13.887
Stolen food.

05:13.887 --> 05:16.679
But who could blame her?
Tough times, right?

05:18.929 --> 05:21.178
She'll only get a year,

05:21.178 --> 05:23.887
maybe two at the most...

05:23.887 --> 05:25.470
when I convict her.

05:27.762 --> 05:30.220
Now, last chance.

05:30.220 --> 05:34.470
Who sold the guns
to Leonard Jensen?

05:39.345 --> 05:40.720
Some guy.

05:40.720 --> 05:41.845
Hmm?

05:41.845 --> 05:43.887
Speak up. Who?

05:43.887 --> 05:45.470
Some guy...

05:45.470 --> 05:47.178
from a bar in Revere.

05:48.136 --> 05:49.553
A guy named Hook?

05:51.345 --> 05:52.512
Yeah.

05:56.762 --> 05:58.387
[door opens]

05:58.387 --> 06:00.095
Wow.

06:00.095 --> 06:03.345
You almost had me believing
you'd have put his ma away.

06:08.679 --> 06:10.303
[laughing]

06:10.303 --> 06:11.845
-Oh, jeez!
-[kids laughing]

06:11.845 --> 06:15.053
Come here! Aah!

06:15.053 --> 06:16.387
Come here, you two
little stinkers.

06:16.387 --> 06:17.679
Come here.

06:17.679 --> 06:19.637
What is going on in here?

06:19.637 --> 06:21.303
All right, all right,
all right.

06:21.303 --> 06:23.428
-My little angel.
-[girl] Grandma got me.

06:23.428 --> 06:25.804
Yeah, well,
that's what wicked witches do.

06:25.804 --> 06:27.887
Come on, I just finished baking.
There's cookies in the kitchen.

06:27.887 --> 06:29.261
Cookies!

06:29.261 --> 06:31.136
All right, be careful.
They're hot.

06:31.136 --> 06:32.428
Don't burn your mouth.

06:32.428 --> 06:33.845
When was the last time

06:33.845 --> 06:35.720
those little shits got a bath?
They stink.

06:35.720 --> 06:37.345
The hot water heater's
still broken.

06:37.345 --> 06:38.970
-What do you want me to do?
-Goddamn it, Cathy.

06:38.970 --> 06:40.720
Didn't I tell you to call
Cyrus DeVany?

06:40.720 --> 06:42.845
Please, the last time
I called him, he charges me $80,

06:42.845 --> 06:44.970
the boiler shits the bed before
he's even back in his truck.

06:44.970 --> 06:46.512
Are you kidding me?

06:46.512 --> 06:48.929
-No, I got to call Pearson's.
-Go ahead.

06:48.929 --> 06:51.178
Spend what little money
you got left.

06:51.178 --> 06:53.345
You know,
because what do I know?

06:53.345 --> 06:55.220
Yeah, exactly.
What do you know?

06:55.220 --> 06:56.553
You know what
you actually are?

06:56.553 --> 06:57.929
You're one of those
fortune-telling machines

06:57.929 --> 06:58.970
down at the carnival.

06:58.970 --> 07:00.595
I don't feel so good.

07:00.595 --> 07:02.929
What is this, your bullshit way
of trying to win this argument?

07:02.929 --> 07:04.387
Cathy, I don't feel right.

07:04.387 --> 07:06.136
Yeah, well,
join the frigging club.

07:06.136 --> 07:09.387
C-Can't catch my breath.

07:09.387 --> 07:11.303
What? What do you need?

07:11.303 --> 07:13.804
I can't breathe.

07:13.804 --> 07:15.470
All right, all right, all right.
Come here.

07:15.470 --> 07:17.178
All right, look at me.
Hey.

07:17.178 --> 07:18.804
Dottie, look at me.
Dottie!

07:23.136 --> 07:24.970
She hasn't been good
to herself, Frankie.

07:24.970 --> 07:27.345
I keep telling her,
but she won't listen.

07:27.345 --> 07:28.970
Doctors are saying
she ain't eating right.

07:28.970 --> 07:31.970
Too many smokes.
Too many gin and tonics.

07:31.970 --> 07:34.804
Her blood pressure's
sky-high.

07:34.804 --> 07:36.303
It's diabetes.

07:38.303 --> 07:40.929
They're saying they may have
to cut off your mom's feet.

07:44.053 --> 07:46.345
[sighs]
Frankie...

07:46.345 --> 07:48.804
I got no insurance.

07:48.804 --> 07:50.720
I can't pay
for none of this.

07:53.011 --> 07:55.220
I got it, Pops.

07:55.220 --> 07:56.679
I'll fix it.

07:58.178 --> 07:59.679
Lawyer.

08:00.929 --> 08:02.178
[sighs]

08:03.387 --> 08:05.136
Hey, lawyering up
is your right.

08:05.136 --> 08:07.512
So, fuck it. Call your guy.
Burn up your cash.

08:07.512 --> 08:10.720
But lawyers are not permitted
to participate in a grand jury,

08:10.720 --> 08:12.845
which is where this thing
is leading.

08:12.845 --> 08:15.929
You ever been indicted,
Mr. Hook? Hmm?

08:15.929 --> 08:18.136
Lawyer.

08:18.136 --> 08:20.011
Hmm.

08:21.679 --> 08:23.929
♪♪

08:40.887 --> 08:42.553
Lawyer.

08:46.387 --> 08:47.720
[wheezing]

08:47.720 --> 08:49.553
[whispering]
Ma.

08:49.553 --> 08:52.470
I thought these might
cheer you up a little bit.

08:52.470 --> 08:54.178
I'm not in the mood
to be cheered up.

08:55.845 --> 08:57.679
[Jimmy]
How's my guardian angel?

08:57.679 --> 08:59.512
-Jimmy.
-Hey, Ma.

08:59.512 --> 09:00.929
[laughs] Hey.

09:00.929 --> 09:02.011
[Jimmy]
Hey.

09:02.011 --> 09:04.553
[groaning]

09:06.011 --> 09:08.011
I got this...this...

09:08.011 --> 09:09.220
[laughs]

09:09.220 --> 09:11.428
Look at that.

09:11.428 --> 09:13.762
How'd you know I was dying
for a taste?

09:13.762 --> 09:17.136
How do I know?
Because I pay attention, Ma.

09:17.136 --> 09:19.261
[Frankie]
Guy rolls out of bed at noon,

09:19.261 --> 09:20.804
pinches a beer
from my fridge,

09:20.804 --> 09:22.553
and you treat him like Bobby Orr
on a breakaway?

09:22.553 --> 09:24.804
Yeah? What'd you bring?

09:24.804 --> 09:27.095
I brought the checkbook,
as usual, Jimmy.

09:27.095 --> 09:28.428
That's fucking good.

09:29.553 --> 09:32.053
-Here. C'mon.
-Nice.

09:32.053 --> 09:33.595
[sniffles]

09:33.595 --> 09:35.261
Is this Steve?

09:35.261 --> 09:36.428
[Steve, on phone]
Yeah. Hey, Frankie.

09:36.428 --> 09:38.470
Ah, my mother took ill, so...

09:38.470 --> 09:41.220
uh, I'm stuck at the hospital
right now for a little bit.

09:41.220 --> 09:43.261
Can you get someone
to cover my-- my shift?

09:43.261 --> 09:45.762
Of course. Hey, you hear
what happened at the Ebb Tide?

09:45.762 --> 09:47.095
No.

09:47.095 --> 09:49.053
A statie and a sheriff
waltzed in,

09:49.053 --> 09:50.261
arrested Hook.

09:52.762 --> 09:54.095
♪♪

09:54.095 --> 09:55.220
Frankie, you there?

09:56.970 --> 09:59.095
Yeah, hey, Stevie,
that's my mother calling.

09:59.095 --> 10:01.428
I got to go. Thanks.

10:05.220 --> 10:06.553
Fuck!

10:06.553 --> 10:08.303
What the fuck?

10:08.303 --> 10:09.804
They arrested Hook.

10:11.970 --> 10:14.136
Oh, fuck!

10:14.136 --> 10:15.970
What the fuck
are we going to do?

10:15.970 --> 10:17.470
Huh?

10:18.970 --> 10:21.387
So, uh, at school,

10:21.387 --> 10:23.261
my first paper...

10:24.303 --> 10:25.845
I got an "A"-plus.

10:25.845 --> 10:27.011
[Jackie]
Oh.

10:27.011 --> 10:28.762
Wow.

10:28.762 --> 10:30.303
Only "A" I ever got?

10:30.303 --> 10:31.679
Detention.

10:31.679 --> 10:33.303
[laughs]

10:33.303 --> 10:34.929
[Bennie] So, uh,
why did you stop studying

10:34.929 --> 10:36.970
for your teaching degree
in the first place?

10:36.970 --> 10:39.428
Because you came along.

10:39.428 --> 10:41.011
Great.

10:41.011 --> 10:43.553
Great, keep putting
that shit on me.

10:43.553 --> 10:46.345
Bennie, come on, you were worth
the change in plans, hon.

10:49.428 --> 10:51.178
What was this paper
all about?

10:52.512 --> 10:54.679
From my comparative
psychology class.

10:55.428 --> 10:56.804
Yeah, the, uh--

10:56.804 --> 10:59.470
the conflicting theories
between Jung and Freud.

10:59.470 --> 11:01.679
It took me forever.

11:01.679 --> 11:03.845
See, while Freud
divided the psyche--

11:03.845 --> 11:07.261
I raise my glass a lot,
I know.

11:07.261 --> 11:10.178
But I raise it tonight

11:10.178 --> 11:12.387
to my amazing daughter
and her A-plus.

11:12.387 --> 11:14.303
[Jenny] Oh, boy.

11:14.303 --> 11:16.345
[doorbell rings]

11:16.345 --> 11:18.345
Who the hell's that?

11:18.345 --> 11:19.887
Sit. Eat. I got it.

11:19.887 --> 11:21.512
[pounding on door]

11:23.970 --> 11:26.387
[doorbell, banging on door
continue]

11:27.595 --> 11:29.387
What the fuck
are you doing here?

11:29.387 --> 11:31.011
You didn't fucking
call me.

11:31.011 --> 11:32.679
You can't come
to my motherfucking--

11:32.679 --> 11:33.720
Jackie.

11:34.512 --> 11:36.220
I'm pregnant.

11:36.220 --> 11:38.011
-Jackie, what's going on?
-Nothing, no, no.

11:38.011 --> 11:39.637
She's-- she's just someone
that came to me for help.

11:39.637 --> 11:41.553
-She's confused.
-He wants to kill our baby.

11:41.553 --> 11:43.887
No, no, no. Shh, shh.
Let's go. Come here. Come here.

11:43.887 --> 11:45.637
-Hon, c'mere, it's okay.
-Hey, what are you doing?

11:45.637 --> 11:47.428
No, whoa, whoa.
Wait a second.

11:47.428 --> 11:48.679
No, no, she's not
coming in here.

11:48.679 --> 11:50.553
No, you can't--
She can't come--

11:50.553 --> 11:52.178
You fucking scumbag
son of a bitch.

11:52.178 --> 11:53.595
-What?
-Ma knew.

11:53.595 --> 11:55.178
She tried to warn me.
I didn't listen.

11:55.178 --> 11:57.845
How the fuck could you
bring your shit to my doorstep?!

11:57.845 --> 11:59.929
-We were just having a nice--
-Get out now!

11:59.929 --> 12:01.303
I don't have any clothes!

12:01.303 --> 12:04.762
Yeah? Then go fucking naked!

12:23.428 --> 12:26.261
FBI man Jackie Rohr.

12:26.261 --> 12:27.553
No bags?

12:27.553 --> 12:29.136
Not staying long?

12:29.136 --> 12:30.762
Not up to me at present.

12:30.762 --> 12:32.512
The usual?

12:32.512 --> 12:33.929
Sure.

12:36.762 --> 12:38.261
No. Uh...

12:38.261 --> 12:40.762
no, you know,
not tonight.

12:42.303 --> 12:43.679
No brunettes.

12:43.679 --> 12:44.970
[laughs]

12:52.845 --> 12:54.595
Do I know you?

12:54.595 --> 12:57.136
You look familiar.
Where are you from?

12:57.136 --> 12:58.970
North Shore.

12:58.970 --> 13:01.136
I could have got that
from the hoops. What part?

13:01.136 --> 13:02.679
Fuck do you care?

13:02.679 --> 13:04.387
Just thought I knew you.

13:04.387 --> 13:06.428
No, you don't.

13:06.428 --> 13:07.929
I don't talk to reporters.

13:07.929 --> 13:10.261
Well, you would be the only cop
in the city

13:10.261 --> 13:12.387
-not willing to talk to me.
-Well, maybe that's because

13:12.387 --> 13:14.637
I'm not interested in a kneeler
out beyond the fens.

13:17.679 --> 13:19.720
One broad to another here?

13:19.720 --> 13:21.261
You got yourself
a nice little job

13:21.261 --> 13:23.053
being an investigator
on this grand jury.

13:23.053 --> 13:25.887
Now, I understand why the county
and the state are involved,

13:25.887 --> 13:27.970
but what makes this
a federal case?

13:27.970 --> 13:30.053
Why is the FBI all over
some four-year-old

13:30.053 --> 13:31.637
missing person bullshit?

13:31.637 --> 13:33.428
No clue what
you're talking about.

13:33.428 --> 13:35.679
No, you know what I'm talking
about when I say Jackie Rohr?

13:38.595 --> 13:40.637
I am done with you.

13:40.637 --> 13:42.011
Look, I respect
what you're doing.

13:42.011 --> 13:43.720
Keeping your mouth shut.

13:43.720 --> 13:45.387
It's your own version
of the code of silence.

13:45.387 --> 13:47.136
But the Boston FBI
is the most corrupt

13:47.136 --> 13:49.804
law enforcement body
in the history of this country.

13:49.804 --> 13:52.970
And think, Jackie Rohr
is their John Wayne?

13:54.845 --> 13:56.470
Wait a minute.
Are you fucking him?

13:58.804 --> 14:00.804
Are you? Have you?

14:02.220 --> 14:04.679
[laughs]

14:04.679 --> 14:07.011
Oh, that's what this is, huh?

14:07.011 --> 14:08.887
Jackie would mow
over his own feet

14:08.887 --> 14:10.595
if he thought there was
something in the grass

14:10.595 --> 14:12.804
that he could trade
for something better.

14:12.804 --> 14:15.470
Get ready, Sheriff Benham,
you could be next.

14:15.470 --> 14:17.595
Aw, jeez.
[laughs]

14:17.595 --> 14:19.136
Look at that.

14:19.136 --> 14:20.845
It's fuck-you o'clock
already.

14:20.845 --> 14:22.095
[laughs]

14:22.095 --> 14:23.887
You know the president
of the Senate

14:23.887 --> 14:25.929
said the same thing to me?

14:25.929 --> 14:28.053
[whispering]
And I'm still here.

14:35.220 --> 14:39.178
That reporter bitch
Michaela Freda,

14:39.178 --> 14:41.553
she says that Jackie's gonna
derail us for his own good.

14:41.553 --> 14:43.512
Does she know something
that we don't?

14:45.970 --> 14:48.261
Now I got to sell
all my hoops.

14:48.261 --> 14:49.804
Why?

14:49.804 --> 14:51.929
Because I saw the same ones
on her.

14:51.929 --> 14:53.595
Wait, wait.

14:53.595 --> 14:55.553
Where's the inventory
from the raid?

14:55.553 --> 14:57.428
Uh...

15:04.512 --> 15:07.095
An M16, an M231.

15:08.470 --> 15:10.095
The National Guard armory
in Macon, Georgia,

15:10.095 --> 15:13.553
reported a cache of weapons
stolen this winter.

15:13.553 --> 15:15.261
M16s and M231s.

15:15.261 --> 15:17.679
Hopefully, they match the serial
numbers of what we seized.

15:17.679 --> 15:19.428
There's no AK on the list.

15:21.095 --> 15:23.136
Time to go
to the gun store.

15:23.136 --> 15:24.804
Huh?

15:24.804 --> 15:26.387
The ATF.

15:26.387 --> 15:27.929
[dials]

15:29.345 --> 15:31.387
♪♪

15:36.970 --> 15:38.387
Later.

15:38.387 --> 15:39.929
Hey, sweetheart?

15:39.929 --> 15:41.887
Sweetheart, I want
to talk to you.

15:41.887 --> 15:43.387
About Dad, yeah.

15:44.387 --> 15:46.136
Yeah.

15:47.011 --> 15:48.762
Look, I-I know
you love him.

15:51.095 --> 15:52.970
But what happened
with that woman...

15:54.637 --> 15:56.136
I-I can't live with it.

15:57.637 --> 15:59.470
And I can't forgive.

16:03.053 --> 16:05.804
Look, I've been praying
all night, and I...

16:05.804 --> 16:09.804
I end every prayer
thinking about you, and...

16:09.804 --> 16:11.512
Yeah, you're pissed.
I get you.

16:11.512 --> 16:13.053
No, it's...

16:13.053 --> 16:14.637
Do you really--

16:14.637 --> 16:16.929
In psych class,
we're learning about empathy.

16:16.929 --> 16:18.845
I don't want to hear
about school

16:18.845 --> 16:21.303
or your "A"-fuckin'-plus.

16:21.303 --> 16:23.512
No, you know, and I-I-I get
what you're doing right now,

16:23.512 --> 16:25.136
acting all sincere
and shit,

16:25.136 --> 16:26.762
'cause you want me
to stay with you.

16:26.762 --> 16:28.428
But it's not gonna happen.

16:28.428 --> 16:30.178
I want to live with Dad.

16:31.887 --> 16:36.261
Fine! Fine, you go
and you live with him!

16:36.261 --> 16:39.178
And his bullshit, his lies,
the nights alone!

16:40.804 --> 16:43.679
I haven't done anything
but be a good mother to you.

16:43.679 --> 16:45.845
And this is the payoff?

16:45.845 --> 16:48.261
Oh, you take his side?

16:48.261 --> 16:51.345
Well, I am fucking done
with the both of ya!

16:52.595 --> 16:54.303
Go! Go ahead!

17:06.595 --> 17:08.303
[Jackie]
Rosa.

17:08.303 --> 17:10.387
Hey. Over here.

17:10.387 --> 17:12.887
Wow. Looking good.

17:13.845 --> 17:15.720
Right this way.

17:15.720 --> 17:18.220
Got a table
right over here.

17:20.637 --> 17:22.053
Here, have a seat.

17:26.178 --> 17:28.011
Smoke Darjeeling tea

17:28.011 --> 17:31.387
and a Fonseca Bin 27
ruby port...for you.

17:33.095 --> 17:34.470
Jackie.

17:34.470 --> 17:36.261
This room.

17:37.553 --> 17:38.929
The Dupont. I mean...

17:40.261 --> 17:41.637
-Too much.
-Oh, no, no, no.

17:41.637 --> 17:42.970
Not for you.

17:42.970 --> 17:46.011
Not for what I want
to talk to you about.

17:46.011 --> 17:48.011
A serious and polite
conversation.

17:48.011 --> 17:52.011
Rosa, I think you and I
got off on the wrong foot.

17:52.011 --> 17:53.762
From the day we met.

17:53.762 --> 17:56.845
Well, and I take
all the blame here...

17:56.845 --> 17:59.053
I presented a grossly false
image of myself,

17:59.053 --> 18:00.720
and then I poured on the charm

18:00.720 --> 18:03.053
and I threw money around
like William Randolph Hearst.

18:03.053 --> 18:04.387
It was all bullshit.

18:04.387 --> 18:07.804
But my intentions
were honest.

18:07.804 --> 18:10.261
Honest Jackie Rohr, hmm?

18:10.261 --> 18:12.136
I was nervous. I...

18:12.136 --> 18:15.720
I was afraid that you and Joe
wouldn't give consent,

18:15.720 --> 18:17.303
and by-- by that I mean
you wouldn't bless

18:17.303 --> 18:19.470
me and Jenny
being together.

18:19.470 --> 18:21.637
You didn't have
Joe or me fooled.

18:21.637 --> 18:23.470
I know that.

18:23.470 --> 18:26.887
And that's why I'm here
to tell you that you were right.

18:26.887 --> 18:28.470
You were right all along.

18:30.387 --> 18:32.136
I'm not good enough
for your daughter.

18:33.512 --> 18:36.136
Which you prove
on a daily basis.

18:37.220 --> 18:39.220
What's your play here, Jackie?

18:39.220 --> 18:40.637
Rosa...

18:42.220 --> 18:44.637
with a gun to my head
and St. Peter taking notes,

18:44.637 --> 18:48.303
I will never deny Jenny again.

18:50.220 --> 18:52.136
I want to make this right.

18:53.804 --> 18:56.011
I want to make my girl happy.

18:56.011 --> 18:58.053
I want to come home.

18:58.053 --> 19:01.136
And you could help me
do that.

19:04.053 --> 19:06.512
I want my driver's license back.

19:08.470 --> 19:09.929
I'm a fed.

19:09.929 --> 19:11.512
State took away your license.
What can I do?

19:12.970 --> 19:15.303
I want to drive again.

19:15.303 --> 19:16.845
Rosa, you hit a fucking
school bus.

19:16.845 --> 19:19.178
And I want more port.

19:21.345 --> 19:23.345
Deputy Chung, you're acting
like I'm asking

19:23.345 --> 19:25.679
for the keys
to your house here.

19:25.679 --> 19:27.929
Look, we raided a tenement
in Roxbury.

19:27.929 --> 19:30.887
We seized guns,
guns which match weapons

19:30.887 --> 19:34.095
stolen from a federal armory,
right?

19:34.095 --> 19:37.345
Now, all I want to do
is find out if my case

19:37.345 --> 19:41.220
wing-mans any ongoing operations
the ATF may possibly have

19:41.220 --> 19:43.345
that pertain to AK-47's.

19:43.345 --> 19:46.970
You know? And we can all,
you know, share the wealth.

19:48.303 --> 19:51.136
Very noble and well spoken.

19:51.136 --> 19:53.387
Here's the ugly truth,
Mr. Ward.

19:53.387 --> 19:55.053
There is nothing
I will share

19:55.053 --> 19:57.470
with any agency
in Suffolk County.

19:57.470 --> 19:59.136
Why?

19:59.136 --> 20:01.303
There are so many fucking leaks
in Boston,

20:01.303 --> 20:04.053
you don't even get puddles
when it rains.

20:04.053 --> 20:07.053
This is prophylactic protection
of my agency.

20:13.220 --> 20:14.220
Thank you.

20:15.804 --> 20:17.136
Hey, you're...

20:17.136 --> 20:19.220
what are you, 40...ish?

20:20.428 --> 20:22.261
Yeah, why?

20:22.261 --> 20:25.261
Oh, you must have went through
FLETC down in Glynco, huh?

20:25.261 --> 20:27.178
Yeah, so?

20:27.178 --> 20:29.053
Doug, you know Doug.
Doug Fioritto.

20:29.053 --> 20:30.929
Head instructor
at FLETC.

20:30.929 --> 20:33.887
Come on, you know Doug.
He's a badass overman.

20:33.887 --> 20:35.428
Yeah, he's a legend.

20:35.428 --> 20:36.804
[Decourcy]
Yeah, he's a buddy of mine.

20:36.804 --> 20:38.428
Good buddy of mine.

20:38.428 --> 20:39.970
Now, listen,

20:39.970 --> 20:41.470
you don't want me
calling him

20:41.470 --> 20:44.261
saying one of his foremen
is aiding and abetting

20:44.261 --> 20:46.261
inner-city gun violence, right?

20:46.261 --> 20:48.095
And you don't want him
calling you,

20:48.095 --> 20:49.887
ripping you a new
asshole.

20:49.887 --> 20:51.428
Right?

20:55.720 --> 20:57.470
Do you swear
there will be no leaks?

20:57.470 --> 20:58.970
Yeah.

20:58.970 --> 21:01.762
How'd you know the lead
FLETC instructor?

21:01.762 --> 21:04.762
I don't. I looked up his name
before we came.

21:04.762 --> 21:07.845
Knowledge is power
and commands obedience.

21:07.845 --> 21:09.970
Oh, Jesus,
don't you start quoting.

21:11.637 --> 21:12.970
This is my chance.

21:12.970 --> 21:15.136
My chance at having a life.

21:15.136 --> 21:18.011
A teaching job,
good friends.

21:18.011 --> 21:19.970
A life of my own, okay?

21:19.970 --> 21:22.178
Where my-- my fuckups are mine,
they're not someone else's.

21:22.178 --> 21:25.011
They're not--
not his.

21:25.011 --> 21:26.970
Well, you don't
have a job.

21:26.970 --> 21:29.428
And Jackie's
a good provider.

21:32.637 --> 21:35.303
Did-- Did you
talk to him?

21:35.303 --> 21:37.345
What, me?
No, I hate the bastard.

21:37.345 --> 21:39.428
So, then why the pressure
to take him back, huh?

21:39.428 --> 21:42.762
Because you're not using
that brain of yours.

21:42.762 --> 21:45.428
All that Freud and shit,
and you don't see.

21:45.428 --> 21:48.387
Your heart's beating up
on your brain.

21:48.387 --> 21:50.720
You think he'd fight fair
in a divorce?

21:50.720 --> 21:53.136
Jackie's got
the bank accounts.

21:53.136 --> 21:56.178
How would you buy food
or gas or pay for the lights?

21:56.178 --> 21:58.845
-You couldn't.
-I don't care about the money.

21:58.845 --> 22:00.512
He'll take Bennie.

22:02.220 --> 22:05.637
You missed your chance to stand
on your own like I told you,

22:05.637 --> 22:08.095
but that don't matter now.

22:08.095 --> 22:11.845
His guilt will get you
whatever you want.

22:11.845 --> 22:13.345
A new car.

22:13.345 --> 22:16.345
A diamond fucking tiara.

22:19.512 --> 22:20.845
I don't know, Ma.

22:22.178 --> 22:23.929
I-I-I can't...

22:26.512 --> 22:28.553
This broke my broken heart.

22:29.553 --> 22:30.804
Yeah, well...

22:33.387 --> 22:35.387
be as dramatic as you want.

22:36.553 --> 22:38.887
But not a day goes by

22:38.887 --> 22:42.220
I don't regret letting
your father walk out.

22:42.220 --> 22:46.178
Well, who'd he walk out on,
Ma, huh?

22:47.387 --> 22:49.345
You? Or me?

22:57.011 --> 22:58.637
[knock on door]

22:58.637 --> 23:00.637
Mr. Ward.

23:00.637 --> 23:06.095
What, you, uh-- you don't
call me Decourcy anymore, Andre?

23:06.095 --> 23:08.261
Do you have a minute?

23:08.261 --> 23:10.929
Sure. Anything for the cause.

23:13.220 --> 23:15.011
That's actually
the reason I came.

23:18.637 --> 23:20.345
I'm sure you're aware
of the rumors

23:20.345 --> 23:22.845
surrounding Reverend Fields
and his behavior

23:22.845 --> 23:24.595
with some of the women
in the congregation.

23:24.595 --> 23:26.178
They're not rumors.

23:26.178 --> 23:27.762
I know.

23:27.762 --> 23:30.261
The reason I came
to speak with you is Siobhan.

23:35.387 --> 23:38.178
You spend a lot of time
with my wife, don't you?

23:38.178 --> 23:41.136
Mr. Ward, I really don't know
why you say that like that.

23:41.136 --> 23:42.929
Siobhan is my friend.

23:44.178 --> 23:46.887
-And I'm engaged.
-Hmm.

23:49.679 --> 23:50.804
Okay.

23:52.011 --> 23:53.553
I'm listening.

23:55.136 --> 23:57.345
Siobhan confronted the reverend
with the accusations.

23:57.345 --> 23:59.095
And I bet he didn't
take that well.

23:59.095 --> 24:01.011
He did not.

24:01.011 --> 24:02.804
Worse, he's been

24:02.804 --> 24:04.512
-bad-mouthing Siobhan...
-Hmm.

24:04.512 --> 24:06.679
...to some of the other
members of the coalition.

24:06.679 --> 24:10.053
He's saying she's a lawyer,
so she lies.

24:10.053 --> 24:12.512
And she doesn't
belong with us.

24:12.512 --> 24:16.553
Now, I'm a good Christian,
and I admire Siobhan.

24:17.845 --> 24:20.053
Fields' words upset me.

24:20.053 --> 24:21.679
I tried to speak with him
about it,

24:21.679 --> 24:22.887
and he scoffed at me.

24:22.887 --> 24:24.428
Like he does.

24:26.970 --> 24:29.637
Well, I, um...

24:29.637 --> 24:32.512
I appreciate you
telling me this.

24:32.512 --> 24:35.512
If I were Siobhan's husband,
I'd want to know.

24:39.136 --> 24:40.095
Thank you, Andre.

24:40.095 --> 24:42.095
You're welcome, Decourcy.

24:45.804 --> 24:47.845
[indistinct PA announcement

24:52.679 --> 24:54.261
Why are you so nervous? Hmm?

24:54.261 --> 24:55.345
Why am I so--? I--

24:55.345 --> 24:56.845
Are you fucking
kidding me?

24:56.845 --> 24:59.095
She's laying in there
waiting for the saw.

24:59.095 --> 25:01.136
So why don't you go pour
a little gin down her throat?

25:01.136 --> 25:02.345
[scoffs]

25:02.345 --> 25:04.428
Oh, fuck.
Same old story, huh, Frank?

25:04.428 --> 25:07.261
You don't know
how to enjoy yourself.

25:07.261 --> 25:08.679
You're barely even
a fucking human being.

25:08.679 --> 25:11.845
You did everything the right way
your entire life,

25:11.845 --> 25:13.345
-and look where it's got you.
-It's got me about ready

25:13.345 --> 25:14.387
to punch you
in your fucking head.

25:14.387 --> 25:15.762
[Jimmy] Fuck you,
you piece of shit!

25:15.762 --> 25:17.095
You think I'm
fucking scared right now?

25:17.095 --> 25:18.387
All right!

25:18.387 --> 25:19.553
-I'll fucking go right now.
-All right!

25:19.553 --> 25:21.220
-Shut up, both of you.
-[Jimmy] What?

25:21.220 --> 25:24.053
Hey! Back up. You're not going
to say anything?

25:24.053 --> 25:26.053
What do you want me to say?
Dottie's the referee

25:26.053 --> 25:27.887
between these two,
not me.

25:29.720 --> 25:31.512
Ohh, fuck.

25:33.220 --> 25:35.720
What are you two not doing
to fuck with Hook

25:35.720 --> 25:37.387
and these Charlestown assholes?

25:37.387 --> 25:39.220
Does your mouth hole
ever get tired?

25:39.220 --> 25:42.178
It's a gift. How did your
interview with Hook go?

25:42.178 --> 25:43.345
What'd he give us?

25:43.345 --> 25:46.053
Nothing. He's hiring counsel.

25:46.053 --> 25:48.178
Nothing on the AK-47?

25:48.178 --> 25:49.887
What'd I say? No.

25:49.887 --> 25:52.929
All right, let's-let's-let's
think this through.

25:52.929 --> 25:58.261
Where does a 1960s Soviet-made
Kalashnikov come from?

25:58.261 --> 26:01.095
Weapon of choice
of the Vietcong

26:01.095 --> 26:03.053
and the Red Army.

26:04.428 --> 26:05.929
Roxbury gangsters?
I mean...

26:08.970 --> 26:10.428
Hang on.

26:10.428 --> 26:13.178
Was Hook in 'Nam?

26:13.178 --> 26:16.387
Um...no, but his brother was.

26:16.387 --> 26:18.428
-What branch?
-The Corps.

26:18.428 --> 26:20.595
Ah, fucking bingo!

26:20.595 --> 26:23.762
I look like Medusa
with a head full of Pepto.

26:23.762 --> 26:25.595
Oh, come on.

26:25.595 --> 26:27.637
You're going to be gorgeous
by the time I'm done.

26:27.637 --> 26:31.095
You know that hot young doctor,
Davison?

26:31.095 --> 26:32.762
He's going to go insane.

26:32.762 --> 26:34.470
[chuckles]

26:34.470 --> 26:36.762
Why are you being
so nice to me?

26:36.762 --> 26:38.637
You're sick.

26:40.136 --> 26:41.220
What else?

26:42.804 --> 26:43.804
[sighs]

26:45.387 --> 26:48.345
All right,
maybe I got a question.

26:48.345 --> 26:49.970
So ask while I'm still
breathing.

26:53.804 --> 26:55.136
[sighs]

26:55.136 --> 26:59.553
[indistinct P.A. announcement]

26:59.553 --> 27:01.428
How'd you put up
with that shit...

27:03.261 --> 27:05.261
for all those years?

27:05.261 --> 27:07.220
How'd you learn to handle
all this stress

27:07.220 --> 27:08.470
of not knowing
whether your husband's

27:08.470 --> 27:09.970
going to be coming home
for dinner,

27:09.970 --> 27:11.470
or trying to make bail?

27:13.637 --> 27:16.845
So, what, you want to have
a real conversation?

27:16.845 --> 27:19.261
Oh, you know what?
Go fuck yourself, honestly.

27:23.553 --> 27:26.887
Years ago,
Frankie was just a baby.

27:26.887 --> 27:30.762
Jimmy wasn't even a drunken
roll in the hay yet.

27:32.428 --> 27:35.637
Someone from the office...

27:37.136 --> 27:38.720
comes by.

27:38.720 --> 27:40.845
He's with a guy.

27:41.845 --> 27:43.387
He's bleeding.

27:43.387 --> 27:45.136
He's shot in the shoulder.

27:46.637 --> 27:48.845
Says to Richie, you know,

27:48.845 --> 27:51.428
"Can you hide him
for a few days?"

27:53.261 --> 27:56.345
So Richie puts him
in the basement.

27:56.345 --> 27:58.929
I say to Richie
I'm gonna take Frankie

27:58.929 --> 28:02.637
to my mother's for a couple
of days till he's gone.

28:02.637 --> 28:04.220
He says I can't.

28:04.220 --> 28:06.136
Everything's got to look normal.

28:08.553 --> 28:11.387
Anyway, a couple
of days later,

28:11.387 --> 28:15.887
guy from the office comes by,
gets the guy and drives off.

28:15.887 --> 28:20.553
Took me two hours to clean
the bloodstain off the floor.

28:22.345 --> 28:23.929
Richie got an envelope.

28:23.929 --> 28:27.220
We didn't miss a house payment
for a year.

28:33.011 --> 28:34.512
All right.

28:37.387 --> 28:38.970
So how'd you do it?

28:38.970 --> 28:40.595
Hmm?

28:40.595 --> 28:43.095
How'd you get through
those couple of days

28:43.095 --> 28:46.637
not knowing who or what?

28:46.637 --> 28:48.470
How?

28:48.470 --> 28:50.512
I did it out of need.

28:50.512 --> 28:51.720
♪♪

28:51.720 --> 28:53.345
We needed diapers.

28:53.345 --> 28:54.970
We needed a roof.

28:54.970 --> 28:57.595
We needed food.

28:57.595 --> 29:01.762
You know, we all live our life
the way we live it

29:01.762 --> 29:03.637
because we have to.

29:03.637 --> 29:05.553
You want to keep
your family together?

29:07.261 --> 29:09.553
You ignore the stress.

29:09.553 --> 29:11.387
You hide the fear.

29:11.387 --> 29:14.845
You never let your husband
see the worry,

29:14.845 --> 29:17.553
'cause that can
get him killed.

29:19.762 --> 29:22.261
The end of the day,
you have no choice.

29:25.845 --> 29:27.887
Even Rose Kennedy
couldn't escape it.

29:27.887 --> 29:29.053
Yeah.

29:30.970 --> 29:32.804
And four of her kids
are dead.

29:34.261 --> 29:36.804
But she's still going,
ain't she?

29:39.970 --> 29:41.804
[bell tolling]

29:46.470 --> 29:48.220
[grunts] Oh! Foul!
That was a charge!

29:50.303 --> 29:53.011
Morgan, if you screw me
out of a clean fadeaway jumper,

29:53.011 --> 29:54.387
you'll have to move
out of the house.

29:54.387 --> 29:55.637
Hey, you pushed off.

29:55.637 --> 29:58.428
And it's two points.
Check.

30:01.804 --> 30:03.178
Practice your threes.

30:03.178 --> 30:05.762
What are you
teaching this kid?

30:05.762 --> 30:07.553
I'm teaching him
beware of reporters

30:07.553 --> 30:09.303
coming up to you
in public parks.

30:09.303 --> 30:11.679
Hey, use your legs.

30:11.679 --> 30:13.887
Keep your hands straight
on the follow-through.

30:13.887 --> 30:15.178
You can do this.

30:15.178 --> 30:16.553
[Morgan]
Yeah, yeah.

30:16.553 --> 30:19.053
[basketball bouncing]

30:19.053 --> 30:21.679
[Hank] Why the fuck are you
haunting our investigation?

30:21.679 --> 30:23.637
What are you after?

30:23.637 --> 30:25.887
Jackie Rohr.

30:25.887 --> 30:27.720
Over the years,
all of his informants

30:27.720 --> 30:29.720
either go missing
or to the morgue.

30:29.720 --> 30:32.011
I want to know what he's hiding,
and why.

30:32.011 --> 30:34.679
You're like a fucking cicada,
you know that?

30:34.679 --> 30:36.345
Jackie's been doing his shit
for 17 years,

30:36.345 --> 30:37.929
only now you come up
out of the dirt?

30:37.929 --> 30:41.845
We're in the middle of a big
and fragile case.

30:41.845 --> 30:44.428
Go back to your hole
until we call you.

30:44.428 --> 30:45.845
[Morgan]
Hey, Dad! Watch this!

30:48.762 --> 30:50.053
[Hank]
Hey, that's a great shot

30:50.053 --> 30:51.220
[Morgan]
I got a good coach.

30:52.720 --> 30:54.011
Meantime,

30:54.011 --> 30:57.637
stay away from Rachel Benham
and me.

30:59.053 --> 31:00.220
Fucking Rohr.

31:01.720 --> 31:03.679
He's proving the adage.

